#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.37:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga "
msgstr "4. Deities "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 37. Dutiyamittasutta → bhikkhumittasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Dutiyamittasutta "
msgstr "37. A Friend (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.32, sc1
msgctxt "an7.37:1.1"
msgid "“Sattahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo bhajitabbo payirupāsitabbo api panujjamānenapi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when a friend has seven qualities you should associate with, accompany, and attend them, even if they send you away. "

msgctxt "an7.37:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi sattahi? "
msgstr "What seven? "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on vattā. I think the point of the comm’s “vacanakusala” is that “vacana” is frequently used idiomatically in the sense of “admonish, criticize”. Thus it pairs with vacanakkhamo.
msgctxt "an7.37:1.3"
msgid "Piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca vattā ca vacanakkhamo ca gambhīrañca kathaṃ kattā hoti, no ca aṭṭhāne niyojeti. "
msgstr "They’re likable, agreeable, respected, and admired. They admonish you and they accept admonishment. They speak on deep matters. And they don’t urge you to do bad things. "

msgctxt "an7.37:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, sattahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo bhajitabbo payirupāsitabbo api panujjamānenapīti. "
msgstr "When a friend has these seven qualities you should associate with, accompany, and attend them, even if they send you away. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.37:2.1"
msgid "Piyo garu bhāvanīyo, "
msgstr "They’re lovable, respected, and admired, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:2.2"
msgid "vattā ca vacanakkhamo; "
msgstr "an admonisher who accepts admonishment, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:2.3"
msgid "Gambhīrañca kathaṃ kattā, "
msgstr "speaks on deep matters, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: niyojako → niyojaye (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.37:2.4"
msgid "no caṭṭhāne niyojako. "
msgstr "and doesn’t urge you to do bad. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an7.37:3.1"
msgid "Yamhi etāni ṭhānāni, "
msgstr "The person in whom "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.2"
msgid "saṃvijjantīdha puggale; "
msgstr "these things are found is your friend. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.3"
msgid "So mitto mittakāmena, "
msgstr "If you want to have a friend, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.4"
msgid "atthakāmānukampato; "
msgstr "benevolent and compassionate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.5"
msgid "Api nāsiyamānena, "
msgstr "you should keep company with such a person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.37:3.6"
msgid "bhajitabbo tathāvidho”ti. "
msgstr "even if they send you away.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.37:3.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
